FBIS4-45444 "jptdd027__l94022" JPRS-TDD-94-027L JPRS Narcotics 16 June 1994 LATIN AMERICA MEXICO PGR Issues Statement on Alleged Kidnapping by DEA Agents PGR Issues Statement on Alleged Kidnapping by DEA Agents PA1706164194 Mexico City EL FINANCIERO in Spanish 16 Jun 94 p 42 PA1706164194 Mexico City EL FINANCIERO Spanish BFN [Text] The Attorney General's Office [PGR] has provided an explanation of the allegations, which have appeared in diverse national media, that in Ojinaga, Chihuahua, DEA agents kidnapped Modesto Lujan Valladares, who was taken to a penitentiary in Marfa, Texas. 1. No official of this institution has stated that DEA agents engaged in the alleged kidnapping of Lujan Valladares in Mexican territory, thereby violating national sovereignty. 2. It has been learned that Modesto Lujan Valladares was arrested on 21 April in Marfa, Texas, near the town of Presidio, which borders Ojinaga, Chihuahua. Lujan Valladares was found in a vehicle, with Victor Valle Lujan, Isidro Armendariz Morales, and Samuel Garcia Wilfar, ready to sell 125 pounds of marijuana to an undercover agent. 3. Nevertheless, the PGR has initiated an investigation into the affair, instructing its representatives in the United States to obtain detailed information on the case to totally clear up the facts for the public. Regarding Sovereignty The unrestricted respect for sovereignty in our nation and the decided struggle against international crime constitute an irrevocable commitment, which the PGR reaffirms to guarantee the community's security.
